Q: Why is it important to know the pKa of an acid?
A: The pKa of an acid can be important in determining its usefulness in certain pharmaceuticals. Certain pharmaceutical drugs may be designed to mimic the effects of an acid, but they are not active until the acid is converted to its active form. If the active form of an acid has an extreme pKa value, then it may be difficult for the drug to be converted and thus its effectiveness would be decreased.
